Testing Techniques - 

ECP - we can use to validate OTP by creating equal no. of classes in input set of test data 
ex - Invalid	Invalid		Valid		Valid
	digits>=7	digits<=5	digits=6	digits=6
	1234567		12345		112233		123456
	
	
BVA - Here we take the values from input set of test data which are on extreme edge or boundary.
Ex - 

Boundary Value Analysis is better than Equivalence Partitioning as it considers both positive
and negative values along with maximum and minimum value.

		Example: Consider a system that accepts ages from 18 to 56.

Boundary Value Analysis(Age accepts 18 to 56)

Invalid 				Valid					Invalid
Min-1		Min, Min+1,Nominial,Max-1,Max		Max+1
17					18, 19, 37, 55, 56			57

	

Valid Test cases: Valid test cases for the above can be any value entered greater than 17 and less than 57.

Enter the value- 18.
Enter the value- 19.
Enter the value- 37.
Enter the value- 55.
Enter the value- 56.
Invalid Testcases: When any value less than 18 and greater than 56 is entered.

Enter the value- 17.
Enter the value- 57.


